  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Kubectl describe pods id only has top level pod information, without any information related to containers. Taking kube-dns pod as an example, which has 3 containers specified: \n\n```\n$ cluster/kubectl.sh describe pods kube-dns-gziey\ncurrent-context: \"golden-system-455_kubernetes\"\nRunning: cluster/../cluster/gce/../../cluster/../_output/dockerized/bin/linux/amd64/kubectl describe pods kube-dns-gziey\nName:               kube-dns-gziey\nImage(s):           quay.io/coreos/etcd:v2.0.3,kubernetes/kube2sky:1.1,kubernetes/skydns:2015-03-11-001\nHost:               kubernetes-minion-p1yo.c.golden-system-455.internal/\nLabels:             k8s-app=kube-dns,kubernetes.io/cluster-service=true,name=kube-dns\nStatus:             Running\nReplication Controllers:    kube-dns (1/1 replicas created)\nConditions:\n  Type      Status\n  Ready     True \nNo events.\n```\n\nIf a pod with RestartAlways policy, but all contianers are in crashloop, the user cannot interpret the true state based on above information. Proposed to include ContainerStatus here. \n",
